The Sandhi Engine Software simulates the rules of Sandhi as discussed by Varadaraja in the Laghu Siddhanta Kaumudi. Effort has been taken to incorporate all rules even those which are applicable to only one unique pair 
of words( for example aksha + uhinI = akshauhiNI not akshohiNI) amongst the innumberable forms possible.
\par 
\par However, rules which make Coding difficult especially ones which apply to all inflected forms of a Noun or Verb are left out as this is a Sandhi Simulator not a Declension Engine.
\par 
\par In the preparation of this Work I was hugely dependant upon Swami Dayanad Saraswati's 'Sandhi Niyma' and  Vaidya Bhimsena Shastri's Hindi Translation and Explanation of the LSK. I also consulted Prof. Ram Sharma's English Tra
nslation of the Ashtadhyayi along with the Hindi translation of Brahma Dutaa Jijnasu. Without these books especially the Bhaimi Vyakhya - which is a mine of lucidity and comprehenive explanations -  I would not have been able to easily create this Softwar
e.
\par 
